The troops of Operation Lafiya Dole, under the subsidiary Operation Kantana Jimlan,  have killed 17 Boko Haram/Islamic State’s West Africa Province terrorists during an encounter along Damboa-Maiduguri road. The coordinator, Defence Media Operations, Major General John Enenche said the troops of 25 Task Force Brigade deployed at Damboa in conjunction with elements of Sector 2 Special Forces on Tuesday, July 7, 2020,  while on clearance operations along Damboa -Maiduguri Road, came in contact with a Boko Haram/Islamic State’s West Africa Province terrorists ambush team along their axis of advance. He said the troops engaged the criminals with overwhelming volume of fire power forcing them to withdraw in disarray. “In the aftermath of the encounter, 17 Boko Haram/Islamic State’s West Africa Province criminals were neutralized as several others were believed to have narrowly escaped with varying degrees of gunshot wounds while a cache of arms and ammunition were equally captured by the gallant troops. “Regrettably, 2 valiant soldiers paid the supreme price while 4 others were wounded in action,” he said. He added that the wounded in action soldiers have been evacuated to a military medical facility and currently responding positively to treatment. The military high command has therefore directed the Theatre Commander Operation LAFIYA DOLE  to immediately deploy a Special Forces Battalion to reinforce and dominate Damboa – Bulabulin – Maiduguri axis to completely deny the terrorists any chance of escape  during the final assault against the criminals. The Defence Headquarters has also urged members of the general public particularly residents of the area to remain calm, law abiding and continue with their routine activities. 